Mineral Resources Minister Mosebenzi Zwane says it's wrong to say that he never consulted with the party. JOHANNESBURG - Mineral Resources Minister Mosebenzi Zwane says it's not true that he failed to consult the African National Congress (ANC) on the new Mining Charter.Last week, the ANC requested an urgent meeting with Zwane following his release of the Mining Charter with has increased the black ownership target to 30%.ANC spokesperson Zizi Kodwa told News24 the ruling party s economic transformation committee wanted to meet with Zwane because it was concerned about the impact the raised level of black ownership could have on jobs in the sector.But Zwane says he hasn't met with the committee yet. The president had already requested me to come to this meeting and we ll go back and engage with the ANC. He says it's wrong to say that he never consulted with the party. I have consulted up to the top six officials and all of them agreed with this charter. Reacting to Chamber of Mines' legal bid to challenge the charter, the minister says he s prepared to head to court to defend his department.(Edited by Winnie Theletsane)